11/01/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The leaders of the three ruling parties -- Ivo Sanader of the Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ), Josip Friscic of the Croatian Peasants Party and Djurdja Adlesic of the Croatian Social Liberal Party (HSLS) -- announced on Thursday (January 10th) the complete list of new government members. The new cabinet has 15 ministries and a total of 18 members, including the prime minister. There will be four deputy prime ministers, with two from the HDZ, one from the HSLS and one representing the Independent Democratic Serb Party. This marks the first time a representative of the Serb minority will serve in a cabinet since Croatia became independent. (Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 11/01/08; HINA, HRT - 10/01/08)
